title: The Wuzzles
creator: Carson Van Osten
description: This cartoon series followed the adventure of the Wuzzles, colorful and playful creatures that were part one animal, part another

title: Adventures of the Gummi Bears
creator: Michael Eisner, Jymn Magon
description: A group of reclusive humanoid bears and a few trusted humans explore their lost heritage and prevent their enemies from exploiting it.

title: DuckTales (1987)
creator: Jymn Magon
description: The globe-trotting treasure-hunting money-making adventures of billionaire Scrooge McDuck and his nephews.

title: The New Adventures of Winnie the Pooh
creator: Karl Geurs
description: Follow Winnie the Pooh's adventures in the Hundred Acre Wood.

title: Chip 'n Dale: Rescue Rangers
creator: Tad Stones, Alan Zaslove
description: Disney's fun-loving chipmunks are re-imagined as the leaders of a team of pint-sized crime-fighters.

title: TaleSpin
creator: Jymn Magon, Mark Zaslove
description: Baloo the Bear from The Jungle Book is cast as a 1930s Pacific Islands bush pilot.

title: Darkwing Duck
creator: Tad Stones
description: A bumbling superhero battles crime with the help of his daughter and pilot sidekick.

title: Goof Troop
creator: Robert Taylor, Michael Peraza Jr.
description: The classic Disney character Goofy is a single father raising his son, Max, in Spoonerville. Pete, a frequent antagonist from the old cartoons, lives next door with his family.

title: The Little Mermaid
creator: Jamie Mitchell
description: The 1989 animated feature adapted by Disney for television in a prequel that leads up to the events of the movie.

title: Raw Toonage
creator: Larry Latham, Ed Wexler
description: An animated anthology featuring various Disney characters.

title: Bonkers
creator: Larry Latham, Duane Capizzi, Robert Taylor
description: Bonkers, an out of work cartoon, joins the Hollywood PD and helps his partners (first a doughnut munching stressbomb, then a beautiful blonde) catch cartoon criminals.

title: Marsupilami
creator: Andre Franquin, Ed Wexler
description: The often off the wall, nonsensical antics of an animated creature with an enormously long tail and his life in the jungle.

title: Aladdin
creator: Tad Stones, Alan Zaslove
description: Aladdin, the clever hero of Agrabah, continues his adventures with the help of his fiancee Princess Jasmine, his pet monkey Abu, Magic Carpet, Iago the greedy parrot, and of course his best friend the semi-cosmic Genie.

title: Gargoyles
creator: Greg Weisman, Michael Reaves
description: A clan of heroic night creatures pledge to protect modern New York City as they did in Scotland one thousand years earlier.

title: The Shnookums and Meat Funny Cartoon Show
creator: Bill Kopp
description: A showcase of animated shorts by Disney.

title: Timon and Pumbaa
creator: Bobs Gannaway, Tony Craig
description: The further misadventures of the lovable warthog Pumbaa and his meerkat buddy Timon from The Lion King (1994).

title: Quack Pack
creator: Toby Shelton, Kevin Hopps
description: The misadventures of Donald Duck and his rebellious teenage nephews with attitude, Huey, Dewey, and Louie.

title: Mighty Ducks: The Animated Series
creator: Marty Isenberg, Robert N. Skir, David Wise
description: A team of humanoid duck ice hockey team/freedom fighters fight evil between games.

title: Disney's Doug
creator: Jim Jinkins
description: The life of a young boy as he meets friends, falls in love, maneuvers his way through grade 6 and writes all about it in his journal.

title: Jungle Cubs
creator: Mark S. Bernthal
description: Here's your chance to see what the animals from 'The Jungle Book (1967)' were like when they were cubs.

title: Nightmare Ned
creator: Terry Shakespeare, Sue Shakespeare, David Molina
description: A Disney show about a timid and imaginative bespectacled eight-year-old boy who, when asleep, must face his daily worries and fears through his strange and often funny nightmares.

title: 101 Dalmatians: The Series
creator: Jim Jinkins, David Campbell
description: Lucky, Cadpig, Rolly, and Spot have a series of adventures around the Dearly Farm.

title: Recess
creator: Paul Germain, Joe Ansolabehere
description: Comic tales of a group of good friends, four boys and two girls, during breaks in primary school, as they grow up, relate to each other, and have brushes with authority.

title: Pepper Ann
creator: Sue Rose
description: The quirky adventures of a 12-year-old girl trying to get through life with her family and friends.

title: PB&J Otter
creator: Jim Jinkins
description: Peanut, Jelly, and Baby Butter are three young otters who live on Lake Hoohaw with their family and friends.

title: Hercules: The Animated Series
creator: Tad Stones
description: This spin-off of Disney's Hercules (1997) follows Hercules' many labors during the years he spent training how to be a hero under the tutelage of satyr Philoctetes. Olympian Gods and Goddesses, as well as Hades and Pegasus, often visit him.

title: Mickey Mouse Works
creator: Bobs Gannaway
description: The continuing adventures of Mickey and friends.

title: The Weekenders
creator: Doug Langdale
description: The humorous Friday through Sunday misadventures of four best friends.

title: Clerks: The Animated Series
creator: David Mandel, Scott Mosier, Kevin Smith
description: The continuing adventures of clerks Dante and Randal, who try to make the best of their menial labor, with no help from Jay and Silent Bob.

title: Teacher's Pet
creator: Gary Baseman, Bill Steinkellner, Cheri Steinkellner
description: Envying the life of his eight-year-old master, a talking dog disguises himself as a human boy in order to go to school with him, and he becomes the big mutt on campus.

title: Buzz Lightyear of Star Command
creator: Mark McCorkle, Bob Schooley
description: The further adventures of Buzz Lightyear as a Space Ranger of Star Command and his comrades.

title: House of Mouse
creator: Bobs Gannaway, Tony Craig
description: Collections of short cartoons hosted by Mickey and his Disney pals at his club, The House of Mouse.

title: Lloyd in Space
creator: Paul Germain, Joe Ansolabehere
description: A Disney show centered around Lloyd, an alien, living in space and going through "ordinary" life with family and friends as a 12 year old.

title: The Legend of Tarzan
creator: Bob Roth, Bill Motz
description: The further adventures of the jungle hero Tarzan (1999) and his friends.

title: Teamo Supremo
creator: Phil Walsh
description: The show tells of three superhero children: Captain Crandall, Skate Lad, and Rope Girl. These three protect their state from all sorts of supervillains.

title: Kim Possible
creator: Mark McCorkle, Bob Schooley
description: A high school cheerleader and her clumsy best friend balance their duties as global crime-fighters with the typical challenges of adolescence.

title: Fillmore!
creator: Scott M. Gimple
description: Former delinquent now fights for the good guys at X Middle School.

title: Lilo and Stitch: The Series
creator: Bobs Gannaway, Jess Winfield
description: The rambunctious human and alien duo must hunt down Dr. Jumba Jookiba's 625 other experimental creatures infesting Hawaii.

title: Dave the Barbarian
creator: Doug Langdale
description: Follow the adventures of Dave, one incredibly unusual barbarian, who's more interested in raising his family and cooking yummy gourmet meals than conquering new lands.

title: Brandy & Mr. Whiskers
creator: Russell Marcus
description: A snobbish dog named Brandy Harrington and a dim-witted rabbit named Mr. Whiskers try to make the best of things when they get stranded in the Amazon rainforest together.

title: Super Robot Monkey Team Hyperforce Go!
creator: Ciro Nieli
description: A twelve-year-old boy named Chiro was exploring the outskirts of Shuggazoom City and discovered a giant and abandoned Super Robot.

title: American Dragon: Jake Long
creator: Jeff Goode, Eddie Guzelian, Matt Negrete
description: A teenage slacker is given the ability to turn into the American Dragon and defends all mythical creatures that secretly reside in the human world.

title: The Buzz on Maggie
creator: Dave Polsky
description: Maggie Pesky is a fun-loving, energetic, creative, and independent thinking tween fly from the metropolis of Stickyfeet, who often ruffles antennae with other insects caught up in conventional, hard-working everyday routines.

title: Get Ed
creator: Andy Knight
description: In the distant future, a popular courier service is threatened by an evil mastermind known as Dr. Bedlam, who has plans for the stalwart company, especially its artificially superhuman member simply named Ed.

title: The Emperor's New School
creator: Mark Dindal
description: Continuation of 2000's The Emperor's New Groove, showcasing Kuzco's attempts to graduate from his kingdom's school, and his former advisor Yzma's evil attempts to keep him from his goal.

title: Mickey Mouse Clubhouse
creator: Bobs Gannaway
description: Mickey and his friends Minnie, Donald, Pluto, Daisy, Goofy, Pete, Clarabelle and more go on fun and educational adventures.

title: The Replacements
creator: Dan Santat
description: Two orphans are given access to a super foster agency that enables them to replace people in their life with aces and superhumans.

title: Shorty McShorts' Shorts
creator: Barry Blumberg, John Solomon
description: Shorty McShorts hosts a series showcasing various low budget cartoon pilots and shorts.

title: Yin Yang Yo!
creator: Bob Boyle
description: Two rabbit siblings are trained by their panda mentor in the mystic martial art of Woo-Foo, in hopes that they can protect the world from ever-present evil forces.

title: My Friends Tigger & Pooh
creator: Brian Hohlfield
description: A girl and her dog have adventures with tigger and pooh in the hundred acre woods

title: Phineas and Ferb
creator: Dan Povenmire, Jeff "Swampy" Marsh
description: Phineas and Ferb invent, scheme, and stay one step ahead of their bratty sister. Meanwhile, their pet platypus plots against evil Dr. Doofenshmirtz.

title: Special Agent Oso
creator: Ford Riley
description: A kids' show centered around a special agent-in-training needs the help of viewers at home in order to complete his missions.

title: Kick Buttowski: Suburban Daredevil
creator: Sandro Corsaro
description: A satirical look at an 8-year-old boy who aspires to be the most hardcore daredevil in existence.

title: Fish Hooks
creator: Noah Z. Jones
description: Three friends attend a school for fish submerged in a pet shop.

title: Take Two with Phineas and Ferb
creator: Dan Povenmire, Jeff "Swampy" Marsh
description: Animated characters Phineas and Ferb interview live-action celebrities on their talk show.

title: Jake and the Never Land Pirates
creator: Bobs Gannaway
description: An animated TV show that follows a band of young pirates who spend their days competing against Captain Hook and Mr. Smee for treasure.

title: Motorcity
creator: Chris Prynoski, David Bickel
description: A fictitious futuristic Detroit, which is an elevated metropolis built over the old Detroit, classified as Detroit Deluxe. It is owned by evil billionaire Abraham Kane.

title: Tron: Uprising
creator: Edward Kitsis, Adam Horowitz
description: In the computer world of the Grid, a young program joins Tron's fight against their world's tyranny.

title: Gravity Falls
creator: Alex Hirsch
description: Twin siblings Dipper and Mabel Pines spend the summer at their great-uncle's tourist trap in Gravity Falls, Oregon. Although Dipper and Mabel quickly discover the Mystery Shack itself is a hoax, they sense there is something strange about their new town and together they begin to unlock the secrets of Gravity Falls.

title: Randy Cunningham: 9th Grade Ninja
creator: Jed Elinoff, Scott Thomas
description: An ordinary ninth grader is chosen to become The Ninja. He is tasked with protecting the town from evil as well as balancing his school life with friends and homework.

title: Sofia the First
creator: Craig Gerber
description: Sofia is a little girl with a commoner's background until her mom marries the king and suddenly she is royalty.

title: Mickey Mouse
creator: Paul Rudish
description: Mickey Mouse takes on new adventures finding himself in silly situations in different settings.

title: Wander Over Yonder
creator: Craig McCracken
description: Wander is is eager to help anyone in the galaxy, together with his friend Sylvia. Wander's friendliness often angers Lord Hater, who is bent on galactic domination, and his army of Watchdogs.

title: The 7D
creator: Tom Ruegger, Mr. Warburton, Noah Z. Jones
description: Happy, Bashful, Sleepy, Sneezy, Dopey, Grumpy and Doc help Queen Delightful defend the kingdom of Jollywood from an evil (but bumbling) sorcerer couple.

title: Penn Zero: Part Time Hero
creator: Jared Bush, Sam Levine
description: Penn Zero is not your average kid - every day he's zapped into another dimension with his friends to save the world.

title: Star vs. the Forces of Evil
creator: Daron Nefcy
description: Intergalactic warrior Star Butterfly arrives on Earth to live with the Diaz family. She continues to battle villains throughout the universe and high school, mainly to protect her extremely powerful wand, an object that still confuses her.

title: Two More Eggs
creator: The Brothers Chaps
description: Dooble and other weird characters star in a series of shorts parodying a young boy's world.

title: Pickle and Peanut
creator: Noah Z. Jones, Joel Trussell
description: The adventures of two unlikely friends, an emotional pickle and a freewheeling peanut, utilizing a mix of animation and live action.

title: Descendants: Wicked World
creator: Aliki Theofilopoulos, Jennifer Magee-Cook
description: After the coronation, the villain kids Mal (Dove Cameron), Evie (Sofia Carson), Jay (Booboo Stewart), and Carlos (Cameron Boyce) use their one shot at being good while their villainous parents roam the Isle Of The Lost.

title: The Lion Guard
creator: Ford Riley
description: Kion, the son of Simba, leads his friends known as the Lion Guard to protect the Pride Lands.

title: Elena of Avalor
creator: Craig Gerber
description: Princess Elena has saved her magical kingdom, Avalor, from an evil sorceress and must learn to rule as its crown princess. Elena's adventures will lead her to understand that her new role requires thoughtfulness, resilience and compassion.

title: Future-Worm!
creator: Ryan Quincy
description: Meet Danny, inventor of the Time Machine Lunch Box. During its maiden voyage, the lunch box was hurled way into the future, where future scientists discovered a simple worm that they put through their genetic escalator, increasing the worm's intellectual capacity and need for adventure. This worm became FUTURE-WORM. Now he's returned to make sure Danny never has a boring day. One boy. One worm. Together. Into the past, present, and future. ...These are their adventures.

title: Milo Murphy's Law
creator: Dan Povenmire, Jeff "Swampy" Marsh
description: An animated comedy adventure series that follows 13-year-old Milo Murphy, the fictional great-great-great-great grandson of the Murphy's Law namesake.

title: Mickey Mouse Mixed-Up Adventures
creator: Rob LaDuca, Mark Seidenberg
description: Mickey Mouse and his pals Minnie, Pluto, Goofy, Daisy, and Donald take their unique transforming vehicles on humorous high-spirited races around the globe as well as hometown capers in Hot Dog Hills.

title: Rapunzel's Tangled Adventure
creator: Shane Prigmore, Chris Sonnenburg
description: Set between Walt Disney Animation Studios' "Tangled" and its short film "Tangled Ever After," this animated adventure/comedy series unfolds as Rapunzel acquaints herself with her parents, her kingdom and the people of Corona.

title: Billy Dilley's Super-Duper Subterranean Summer
creator: Aaron Springer
description: The show follows the adventures of Billy Dilley, a 12 year old 7th grader who loves science, and his lab partners, Zeke and Marsha, who on summer vacation find themselves trapped in a strange world located in the Earth's core.

title: Ducktales (2017)
creator: Matt Youngberg, Francisco Angones
description: The comedy-adventure series chronicles the high-flying adventures of trillionaire Scrooge McDuck, his grandnephews - Huey, Dewey, and Louie - temperamental nephew Donald Duck, Launchpad McQuack, Mrs. Beakley, and her granddaughter Webby.

title: Big Hero 6: The Series
creator: Mark McCorkle, Bob Schooley, Nick Filippi
description: As the new prodigy at San Fransokyo Institute of Technology, Hiro now faces daunting academic challenges and the social trials of being the little man on campus. Off campus, the stakes are raised for the high-tech heroes as they must protect their city from an array of scientifically enhanced villains.

title: Big City Greens
creator: The Houghton Brothers
description: The adventurous life of Cricket Green, a country boy who moves with his family from their rural farm to a modern metropolis.

title: Fancy Nancy
creator: Anne Smith, Jamie Mitchell, Krista Tucker
description: The story of a young girl who loves to wear fancy clothes.

title: Amphibia
creator: Matt Braly
description: Ordinary Anne Boonchuy, 13, finds a music box that sends her to Amphibia, a world full of frogs, toads, and giant insects. With help from Sprig, she must adjust to life in Amphibia and discover the first true friendship in her life.

title: The Owl House
creator: Dana Terrace
description: Accidentally sent to the world of the Boiling Isles before a trip to summer camp, a teenage human named Luz longs to become a witch and is aided by rebellious Eda and pint-sized demon King.

title: The Wonderful World of Mickey Mouse
creator: Paul Rudish
description: Mickey and his best pals - Minnie, Donald, Daisy, Goofy and Pluto - embark on their greatest adventures yet, navigating the curve-balls of a wild and zany world where the magic of Disney makes the impossible possible.

title: Monsters at Work
creator: Bobs Gannaway
description: Mechanic Tylor Tuskmon has big dreams of working his way up the ranks to the Laugh Floor at Monsters Inc.

title: Mickey Mouse Funhouse
creator: Phil Weinstein, Thomas Hart
description: Funny, an enchanted talking playhouse, leads Mickey Mouse and his pals on imaginative adventures.

title: The Ghost and Molly McGee
creator: Bill Motz, Bob Roth
description: A grumpy ghost named Scratch is eternally cursed to be in the presence of polar opposite Molly McGee, a cheerful tween.

title: Rise Up, Sing Out
creator: Latoya Raveneau, Questlove
description: Features episodes that aim to deliver inspiring and optimistic messages, teaching children about respect towards others, such as celebrating Black hair, and exploring names that can be mispronounced or stigmatized.

title: Alice's Wonderland Bakery
creator: Chelsea Beyl
description: Alice, the great-granddaughter of the original Alice and a budding young baker at the enchanted Wonderland Bakery, where treats bring a new generation of characters together.

title: The Proud Family: Louder and Prouder
creator: Bruce W. Smith, Ralph Farquhar
description: The daily life of Penny Proud as she hilariously navigates growing up in a rambunctious house with a loving mom and an overly protective father.

title: Chibiverse
creator: Gino Guzzardo
description: The series centers on the adventures of "Chibi" versions of Disney characters as they live in their own universe.

title: Hamster & Gretel
creator: Dan Povenmire
description: Gretel and her pet Hamster suddenly receive new superpowers. Now, protective older brother Kevin must figure out how to work with both Gretel and her pet to protect their city from mysterious dangers.

title: Firebuds
creator: Craig Gerber
description: Follow a boy and his fire truck in a fantasy world where talking vehicles live, work and play with the humans who drive them as they team up with their friends and teamwork to help their community.

title: Marvel's Moon Girl and Devil Dinosaur
creator: Steve Loter, Jeffrey M. Howard, Kate Kondell
description: After 13-year-old super-genius Lunella accidentally brings ten-ton T-Rex, Devil Dinosaur into present-day New York City via a time vortex, the duo works together to protect the city's Lower East Side from danger.

title: Kiff
creator: Lucy Heavens, Nic Smal
description: Follow the adventures of best friends Kiff, an optimistic squirrel, and Barry, a mellow bunny, as they take Table Town by storm with their endless adventures.

title: Hailey's On It!
creator: Devin Bunje, Nick Stanton
description: Hailey Banks, a risk-averse but resourceful teenager, is on a mission to complete every item on her long list of tasks in order to save the world.
